In the event of the unfair scottish referendum pointing to independence, England must respond appropriately.

1.  Her Majesty must be respectfully requested to disassociate herself completely from Scotland (No Queen of Scotland);
2.  Her Majesty's government must be required to unequivocally show the legal basis on which Scotland might steal 8.4% of UK assets;
3.  And then it must be required to publish what assets it proposes to allow to be stolen;
4.  And it must submit its proposals to the non-Scottish electorate for approval;
5.  No military equipment may be given to Scotland;
6.  There must be a border impenetrable from the Scottish side. No Scot should be welcome. Minimum visa fee - £500.
